The other day was my day for the “dreaded Glucose test” that typically happens between week 24-28 of pregnancy. I went an alternative route during my pregnancy with Rell so I never experienced the glucola drink, BUT this time my doctor offered a natural alternative to the standard glucose drink, called the Fresh Test. (I have no affiliation with this) It ended up not being so “dreaded” of an experience after all.
It still creates that glucose load with 50g of sugar, but it tastes like a refreshing lemonade and it’s non-gmo, with no additives and preservatives, and I didn’t feel icky at all. (It does warn that some may experience side effects— that is a lot of sugar at once!) I was even able to eat a boiled egg before my test as mine was a non-fasting test, but of course follow what your provider suggests! I mixed the powder with some water and drank it an hour before my blood draw. The visit to the lab was easy. And now I just wait for my results! 🙏🙏
__
I wanted to share this quick experience and just bring awareness that there is a natural alternative that you can explore with your doctor when it’s time for your Glucose Test during pregnancy. Obviously this is an important step for mama and baby during pregnancy, so this is up to you and your doctor, but I personally love learning about other alternatives that feel right to me.

SAVE this for a quick Egg Free Breakfast option!
Rell has never liked eggs- never. Which led us to exploring if there was something instinctual behind it and we learned she had an egg allergy when she was a baby. The great news is, she can eat eggs baked into things, and I think she’s growing out of this allergy BUT she still dislikes eggs. Obviously eggs are an easy and awesome way for quick protein for breakfast— especially in the form of egg bites! SO it was time to explore a new Quick Protein option for breakfast and she LOVES these Sausage bites! We call them “muffins” 😉 Wether you’re catering to an egg allergy in your home or not- this is a great breakfast alternative to keep in your fridge or freezer for when you need a quick and healthy breakfast grab!
*I make these gluten free- and they can easily be made dairy free!
—
RECIPE
-1lb ground Breakfast Sausage
-1-2 cups finely chopped broccoli florets (optional, but a great way to add greens into breakfast!)
-1 cup your choice of gluten free flour (I used Bob’s Red Mill Paleo All Purpose mix)
-1 tsp baking powder
-1 cup shredded cheese- I use goat cheddar. You can simply make this dairy free with a dairy free cheese alternative!
-3/4 cup Almond Milk (or your choice of milk)
—
•Sauté 1 lb breakfast sausage & finely chopped broccoli florets in avocado oil until sausage is fully cooked 
•In a mixing bowl, add 1 cup gluten free flour, 
1 tsp baking powder, & mix together. 
•Then add 1 cup shredded cheese. Mix all together.
•Add and mix in cooked sausage & broccoli to the dry mix. 
•Add 3/4 cup of Almond Milk. Mix together well.
•Scoop mixture into pre-greased cupcake pan- I use avocado oil spray. 
•Bake for 20-25 minutes at 400 degrees.

Enjoy these!! You can store in the fridge for a few days, or freeze them for when needed! Approved by my toddler— and my husband and I love them too!

#eggfreebreakfast #glutenfree #toddlerbreakfast #glutenfreebreakfast

A MUST on your weekly meal rotation! SAVE for this delicious Sausage, Kale, Ravioli soup. This was inspired by another recipe I saw via Instagram, but I made some upgrades to make it Gluten Free and healthier! We use a Grain Free Ravioli- but you can use a gluten free ravioli/tortellini, or any type of Gluten Free Pasta! I suggest a simple pasta if you’re wanting to make this Dairy Free.
Oh, and obviously, wait til it’s cooled down to eat— I basically burned my mouth in the making of this reel!😂
__
Ingredients
-1 lb Spicy or Mild Italian chicken Sausage— I buy this from the meat counter at the grocery store. 
-1 small yellow onion, diced
-5-7 cloves garlic, minced
-3 Tbsp Gluten Free flour (I use Bob’s Red Mill Paleo all purpose flour mix)
-1 tsp dried basil
-½ tsp dried oregano
-a pinch of cayenne (omit if you’re trying to keep the spice level low)
-1 tsp (gluten free) hot sauce (I use Sweet Baby Ray’s hot sauce- equivalent to Franks)
-½ tspmustard powder
-1 cup full fat Coconut Milk (I prefer it canned)
-32 oz Chicken Broth (I used Kettle & Fire)
-2-3 cups organic kale, chopped
-1 Box of @cappellos Grain Free Ravioli (I find this in the freezer section, and try to thaw for a bit before cooking) OR use your choice of gfree pasta or gluten free tortellini!
-Pink Salt and Pepper to taste. 
-optional: pinch red pepper chili flakes
Instructions
-Spray Large pot with Avocado Oil, and cook the sausage (remove the casing if using sausage links) and diced onions, and garlic over medium-high heat until the onions and garlic are softened and the sausage is cooked through.  -Add your gluten free flour and cook for about 2 minutes, to cook the flour in.
-Add basil, oregano, cayenne, hot sauce, and mustard powder. Stir to combine. -Add the chicken broth, add and stir in Coconut Milk. While stirring, “clean” the bottom of the pot.
-Bring to a boil, (if using regular gluten free pasta, add it in now to cook while it’s boiling) Reduce to a simmer. -Add ravioli to cook about 5-8 minutes, depending on its cooking time. Bring to a simmer.
-Add the Kale, and stir it into cook. -Add in red chili flakes, pink salt, pepper to taste!
ENJOY!! ❤️

BROWNIES!!! SAVE this for my gluten free, grain free, dairy free Brownie recipe for a last minute sweet treat to make for someone you Love for Valentine’s Day or to take with you to a Galentine’s gathering! ❤️ These are guilt free but insanely decadent & delicious!! You can cutout into little hearts & drizzle chocolate on top, or pair with some raspberries or strawberries for the extra touch of love!!! RECIPE BELOW!
—
And ohhh my these pictures are from last year shooting with @alexclarkphoto 🥹 I’ve been horrible at collecting moments like these this year, so recycling for now! But feeling super motivated to get some new memories captured before baby sister gets here!

BROWNIE RECIPE ❤️
Ingredients:
• 3/4 cup Coconut Sugar
• 1/3 cup Raw Organic Cacao Powder
•1/4 cup Coconut Oil (melted)
• 1 tsp vanilla extract (gluten free)
• 2 pastured eggs
• 1 cup almond flour
• 1/4 tsp baking powder
• 1/4 tsp sea salt

Instructions
• Blend melted coconut oil, coconut sugar and vanilla in a bowl.
• Add in eggs and mix well with a spoon.
• In a separate bowl combine almond flour, cacao powder, baking powder and salt.
• Gradually blend into egg mixture.
• Spread into a greased 9 inch glass pan (I oiled with coconut
• Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until it pulls away from the edges.
•Cool completely in the pan and ENJOY!
*Mine were just as good chilled, but of course were heavenly when they were “fudgey” right out of the oven!

I Can’t wait for you to make these!! 
 #glutenfree #glutenfreedessert #valentinesdaydessert #galentinesday
